</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="54" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[106,220,912,936]" box="[106,220,912,936]" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[106,220,912,936]" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[106,1095,950,1005]" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">
The specific name is derived from the Greek for “without light” (
<emphasis box="[775,829,950,974]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">aphos</emphasis>
)), referring to the dark colouration of this species with respect to the other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="CZERNY" authorityYear="1903" box="[613,766,982,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Heteromeringia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[613,766,982,1005]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">Heteromeringia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with four fronto-orbitals.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
