<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[107,222,1108,1126]" box="[107,222,1108,1126]" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[107,222,1108,1126]" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">Comments</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[106,1097,1146,1292]" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">
Within the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="KERTESZ ER" authorityYear="1903" box="[231,462,1146,1169]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Heteromeringia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="czernyi">
<emphasis box="[231,462,1146,1169]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">Heteromeringia czernyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lonsdale &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2007" box="[546,683,1146,1170]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Heteromeringia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aphotisma">
<emphasis box="[546,683,1146,1170]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">H. aphotisma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, like 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K ERTESZ" authorityYear="1903" box="[743,848,1146,1169]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Heteromeringia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="czernyiczernyi">
<emphasis box="[743,848,1146,1169]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">H. czernyiczernyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="WILLISTON ILLIST" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[904,1011,1146,1170]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Heteromeringia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipes">
<emphasis box="[904,1011,1146,1170]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">H. flavipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has retained dark colouration and an upcurved bristle in the posterodorsal corner of the anepisternum. Unlike these two dark species, however, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lonsdale &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2007" box="[524,660,1207,1231]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Heteromeringia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aphotisma">
<emphasis box="[524,660,1207,1231]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">H. aphotisma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has an additional reclinate fronto-orbital bristle (synapomorphic of the rest of the group), entirely dusky wings, brown legs (excluding the mid and hind tarsi) and a much darker head, easily separating it.
</paragraph>
